title: Independent Candidate Ali Badi wins PK-96 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): An Independent Candidate Ali Badi has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-96, Kurram-II by securing 38,593 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Wasi Syed Mian who bagged 24,874 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 45.79 per cent.
